This paper deals with the triangulation of dynamic graphical models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the Graphical Model Toolkit (GMTK), which falls under the sub-category cs.SI (Systems and Control). Lastly, the paper mentions the use of dynamic Bayesian networks in speech recognition research systems, which falls under the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
